      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks, i already ran a scan and nothing came up. that's what's tripping me out. it's like the malware is baked into the OS itself, so the antivirus thinks it's a legitimate system process. i was looking into how these updates are structured and it almost looks like they're using the kernel to scrape more than just usage data—like they're trying to capture raw neural/biometric patterns through the hardware interface. do you think it's possible an update could be designed to actually harvest more than just metadata?",
